<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Beor</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-10-21 02:11:49</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Well,<BR>
<BR>
I just got it and have been running around with it on my shaman for the past 10 minutes.  I camped the goblin camp where the casters spawn for 5, yes 5, levels.  That's from lvl 5 to lvl 10.  I was seriously on the verge of giving up tonight when I saw the caster beads ... unshattered.  Yes, it does fit into the ranged weapons slot.<BR>
<BR>
Here's what little advice I can give:<BR>
<BR>
While all the goblins at that camp were blue I just stayed there and killed them sitting in-between.  After they became green -- from I think lvl 6 or at least 7 on -- I would simply killed the goblins during my down times between killing blue, even and yellow snowcats, snoworcs and snowelephants (well ok, leopards or troopers and wooly mammoth calves -- note: most of the mammoth calves are red even at lvl 10).  So anyhow, I would just go fight, go back to goblin camp, kill both goblins, then med, then go fight, rinse, repeat.  I usually sat there and sometimes ran through 2 goblin spawns before being totally back up on hp/mana in order to go take on big stuff.  Basically, just work them into your down time somehow.  I got to where I'd even drag exp mobs back to the camp so that as soon as I killed the big mob I could turn and take out the spawning green goblins when they spawned.  DO NOT waste mana on the goblins after they are well green to you.  But, you do want to make them die as close to one another as possible time wise.  Wait until both spawn.  If 2 scouts (boy I hated the constant stream of scouts) then do the following:<BR>
1. Let both spawn.<BR>
2. Go and sit just outside the doorway to the igloo the one goblin is in.  This will make them both attack you.<BR>
3. Drag them over between the goblin banner-flag and the tree to kill there.<BR>
4. Rinse/Repeat.<BR>
<BR>
You can use the above no matter what spawn or I would sometimes do this if one of the 2 spawns was a caster:<BR>
1. Cast ice strike (only one cast to pull) on the goblin inside the igloo (whether the scout or the caster).<BR>
2. Then untarget it and target the goblin outside that you are standing next to.<BR>
3. If the goblin inside the igloo is a caster this will help pull it out maybe.  It seems sometimes I couldn't get the caster to come out by just sitting, so I would do this if a caster spawned.<BR>
<BR>
Other points of interest:<BR>
-Sometimes, 2 casters spawn.  Don't get excited.  If your experience is like mine you'll have to wait a long time to get the caster beads.<BR>
-Sometimes the goblins (scouts mostly I think) drop turqoise.<BR>
-Sometimes they drop a copper ring.<BR>
-The caster that dropped the caster beads also dropped a malachite and a normal ice goblin necklace as well.<BR>
-Keep all shattered and regular goblin neclaces and when full (I carried 7 backpacks) go perform the ice goblin caster quest (the same one that gives you the gavel of Justice) and the ice goblin necklace quest (warrior lady in the warrior guild).  These will give you some experience and that always helps especially for lower lvls.  Also, you get spells from the shattered caster beads and food and water from warrior lady as well.  This way, even though the goblins are green, you're still getting some exp from killing them albeit not much, but helps trust me.<BR>
<BR>
Ok, well, sorry to write so much.  I hope I gave all the good info I could think of about doing this quest.  I put enough time into it trust me.<BR>
<BR>
Oh, and it does work.  Not broke :)<BR>
<BR>
Beor,<BR>
Shaman now 10th Season,<BR>
Emarr server</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Beor</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-10-21 02:19:37</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Oh, and the reason you want to pull the goblins away from their igloos and between the goblin banner and tree is that sometimes a snow leopard or orc trooper (and even a little goblin whelp) will come meandering through the goblin camp walking right over one of the igloos.  If you're standing their fighting the goblins it will train to you.  At levels 6ish and 7ish the leopard and orc will be red and you'll probably die.  Alway run to that nearby Barb Guard when in trouble.  Don't forget to run diagonal and jump until you get sow :)  And sell the spells you get after you already got all your level 5 spells.  You can get some good money, maybe, from sicken cuz most people don't know you can buy it out in everfrost near the river....<BR>
<BR>
Ok, I'm done for sure now.<BR>
<BR>
Beor,<BR>
Shaman now 10th Season,<BR>
Emarr server</font></td></tr></table>
